Remove and discard any dark parts from the bloodline of the tuna. Finely dice the remaining tuna and place in a large bowl. Stand the bowl on ice to keep chilled.Add the spring onions, chilli and ginger to the tuna and mix well.In a separate bowl mix together the honey, soy sauce, lime juice, sesame oil and toasted sesame seeds.Toast the slices of ciabatta on a griddle pan.To serve, press the tuna tartare into a 7cm/3in chefâ€™s ring on each serving plate. Carefully remove the ring, arrange the toast and lime wedges around the tartare.